Functions:

When a certain steps/ instructions  need to be executed only when it is called for

eg:
def <function name> ()
  write the block of code

Calling a function:
function name(): 

with parameters/arguments:
def <functionname> (param1)
  write the block of code

Calling a function:
functionname(value)

eg:
calculate the hours from days:

no_of_days=30;

def hours():
  print(f"{no_of_days} days has {30*24} hours")

hours()

Passing value:

def hours(no_of_days):
  print(f"{no_of_days} days has {30*24} hours")

hours(20)

multiple values:

def hours(no_of_days,unit):
  print(f"{no_of_days} days has {no_of_days*24} {unit}")

hours(40,"hours")
